he doesn't care about getting a good shot.

1507
01:33:04,560 --> 01:33:07,291
I could talk to the principal and...

1508
01:33:10,479 --> 01:33:12,881
Bo told me tonight.

1509
01:33:17,880 --> 01:33:20,042
I actually have to go, I'm sorry.

1510
01:33:21,000 --> 01:33:23,320
I promised my boyfriend
that I'd meet his family.

1511
01:33:26,000 --> 01:33:27,764
Yeah, you should get going.

1512
01:33:28,760 --> 01:33:30,250
And, Angie, I...

1513
01:33:32,520 --> 01:33:34,363
I want you to be happy.

1514
01:33:40,000 --> 01:33:43,402
Oh, God, what is that?

1515
01:33:45,720 --> 01:33:47,721
There goes the tree.

1516
01:33:48,039 --> 01:33:50,500
Should we intervene? They need a referee?

1517
01:33:50,600 --> 01:33:51,965
- It's disturbing.
- It's not safe.

1518
01:34:22,640 --> 01:34:25,324
Can I tell you something, without
knowing anything about you?

1519
01:34:27,359 --> 01:34:28,645
I think you need Jello.

1520
01:34:32,239 --> 01:34:33,923
You have his smile.

1521
01:34:36,560 --> 01:34:37,640
I got lucky.

1522
01:34:49,199 --> 01:34:53,726
You know, I think that your hands
were the first thing I loved about you.

1523
01:34:57,520 --> 01:34:58,885
I'm gonna miss them.

1524
01:35:01,119 --> 01:35:05,841
I think, at first, I held on so tight
to the kids, because

1525
01:35:07,359 --> 01:35:10,091
of all that we went through
and how much I loved them.

1526
01:35:11,279 --> 01:35:12,280
But now...

1527
01:35:14,119 --> 01:35:16,122
I think I'm holding on because...

1528
01:35:16,920 --> 01:35:19,525
I don't know who I am, if I don't.

1529
01:35:21,800 --> 01:35:23,449
My love for them...

1530
01:35:25,279 --> 01:35:28,568
it's so huge.
I kinda got lost in it, you know?

1531
01:35:30,880 --> 01:35:33,007
And a part of me, like you said...

1532
01:35:34,159 --> 01:35:36,002
- A part of me got small.
- No.

1533
01:35:36,199 --> 01:35:37,280
You're not small.

1534
01:35:37,720 --> 01:35:40,006
I didn't even agree
with me when I said it.

1535
01:35:40,560 --> 01:35:43,689
- You're beautiful and ridiculous.
- No.

1536
01:35:43,840 --> 01:35:46,490
And as passionate as you always were.

1537
01:35:48,039 --> 01:35:50,690
- It's about different things now.
- Yeah.

1538
01:35:52,279 --> 01:35:54,646
We had a great run, Charlotte.

1539
01:35:56,359 --> 01:35:59,283
- Nobody can say we didn't try.
- No, we tried.

1540
01:36:06,359 --> 01:36:09,260
- Let's go on the trip.
- You don't have to.

1541
01:36:09,359 --> 01:36:11,840
No, look at me, honey,
I want to go with you.

1542
01:36:14,840 --> 01:36:15,841
Really?

1543
01:36:17,479 --> 01:36:19,448
That's incredible.

1544
01:36:21,680 --> 01:36:23,648
Oh, Charlotte...

1545
01:36:24,880 --> 01:36:26,962
I don't really know
if we should go to Africa.

1546
01:36:27,520 --> 01:36:30,420
- What?
- Bo said Hank got laid off.

1547
01:36:30,520 --> 01:36:32,648
Oh, my God, I knew it.

1548
01:36:32,880 --> 01:36:34,119
The tell tale snort.

1549
01:36:34,399 --> 01:36:35,560
That snort.

1550
01:36:35,920 --> 01:36:37,159
But, I can...

1551
01:36:38,199 --> 01:36:41,060
take you out to a really amazing dinner.

1552
01:36:41,159 --> 01:36:45,659
We could go to some fancy
Ethiopian place with native dress.

1553
01:36:45,760 --> 01:36:48,899
You can take me to IHOP, for all I care.

1554
01:36:49,000 --> 01:36:50,001
Yeah, me too.

1555
01:36:54,960 --> 01:36:56,199
Oh, my...

1556
01:36:58,840 --> 01:37:01,524
- Hi, Sam.
- Hi.

1557
01:37:20,640 --> 01:37:22,085
Good for them.

1558
01:37:23,159 --> 01:37:26,845
Why waste a moment?
We're here for such a short time.

1559
01:37:52,199 --> 01:37:56,250
I need a last minute gift that
doesn't involve teddy bears,

1560
01:37:57,119 --> 01:37:59,930
balloons or pictures
of children with big eyes.

1561
01:38:00,560 --> 01:38:01,765
You can never go wrong with chocolate.

1562
01:38:02,039 --> 01:38:03,121
No.

1563
01:38:03,720 --> 01:38:08,247
Get me the most expensive thing
that you have.

1564
01:38:12,600 --> 01:38:15,569
You shouldn't have done this.
I feel so ridiculous.

1565
01:38:15,920 --> 01:38:17,206
Here we go.

1566
01:38:20,520 --> 01:38:21,520
Emma, no!

1567
01:38:21,880 --> 01:38:23,220
No, look...

1568
01:38:23,319 --> 01:38:24,320
What?

1569
01:38:25,119 --> 01:38:28,521
That's the most expensive thing they had.

1570
01:38:30,000 --> 01:38:31,684
I really like it.

1571
01:38:31,920 --> 01:38:34,650
'Cause what says Christmas
better than a shower seat?

1572
01:38:34,960 --> 01:38:35,961
Exactly. Well said.

1573
01:38:36,359 --> 01:38:38,840
I could really use that shower seat.

1574
01:38:41,319 --> 01:38:43,845
Merry Christmas. To you, Mom.

1575
01:38:44,279 --> 01:38:45,690
To family.

1576
01:38:47,239 --> 01:38:50,926
Bucky woke up with an unexpected
craving for lime Jello.

1577
01:39:06,640 --> 01:39:08,368
As everyone sat around the table,

1578
01:39:08,640 --> 01:39:11,420
the past, present and future
were coming together

1579
01:39:11,520 --> 01:39:13,408
for one elusive night.

1580
01:39:30,479 --> 01:39:33,563
Fate was kind, playing
that particular muzak just then.

1581
01:39:38,199 --> 01:39:39,500
Excuse me, Madison.

1582
01:39:39,600 --> 01:39:41,966
Might I steal this man away from you?

1583
01:39:42,119 --> 01:39:43,280
Oh, yeah?

1584
01:39:43,920 --> 01:39:45,081
- Can I?
- Mom.

1585
01:39:45,239 --> 01:39:47,260
Sam and Charlotte relished
in the closeness

1586
01:39:47,359 --> 01:39:51,126
brought on by the time well spent
on the trip not yet taken.

1587
01:39:55,119 --> 01:39:56,564
I still got it.

1588
01:40:08,399 --> 01:40:09,480
I've never seen that.

1589
01:40:09,720 --> 01:40:10,720
Are they are really doing this?

1590
01:40:14,920 --> 01:40:18,048
Eleanor let go of her past enough
to be in the present.

1591
01:40:21,520 --> 01:40:23,539
Instead of trying to present
the perfect picture,

1592
01:40:23,640 --> 01:40:26,449
Hank celebrated this moment
un-photoshopped.

1593
01:40:29,279 --> 01:40:31,567
- Do you want to dance?
- Me?

1594
01:40:32,199 --> 01:40:35,043
Hank and Ruby took
their first step on the right foot.

1595
01:40:37,159 --> 01:40:40,050
All the more meaningful, because
Bucky had led them to it.

1596
01:41:13,680 --> 01:41:16,444
And Charlie would always remember
his first kiss.

1597
01:41:16,560 --> 01:41:20,359
His sloppy, awkward, but very first kiss.

1598
01:41:21,720 --> 01:41:24,020
You look pretty, Emma.
Do you want to dance?

1599
01:41:24,119 --> 01:41:25,280
Gosh, I would love to dance.

1600
01:41:25,520 --> 01:41:27,443
I would really love to dance.

1601
01:41:27,560 --> 01:41:31,087
Emma finally recognized she was
already part of a large family.

1602
01:41:34,640 --> 01:41:37,659
As Bucky stood, taking them in,
his family unaware of him,

1603
01:41:37,760 --> 01:41:39,284
this thought entered his head,

1604
01:41:39,399 --> 01:41:41,528
which he shared with a large
Haitian orderly.

1605
01:41:42,239 --> 01:41:43,240
Such a fuss...

1606
01:41:44,760 --> 01:41:48,207
when everything we want is right
in front of us the whole time.

1607
01:41:49,199 --> 01:41:52,601
And at last, everyone
appreciated that very sentiment.

1608
01:41:53,000 --> 01:41:55,570
Why is it they can never remember that?

1609
01:41:56,159 --> 01:42:00,926
Or maybe the point is, even
just for a moment, they do.

1610
01:42:06,319 --> 01:42:08,402
Well, that's my tale.

1611
01:42:10,439 --> 01:42:13,807
Sometimes, I wonder about all
the families sharing dinner together.

1612
01:42:14,520 --> 01:42:15,520
Each house,

1613
01:42:17,000 --> 01:42:17,966
each family,

1614
01:42:19,840 --> 01:42:21,762
each one with stories of their own.

1615
01:42:23,319 --> 01:42:26,210
I don't know who chooses
our families for us.

1616
01:42:26,800 --> 01:42:29,451
Or if there's a reason
we land where we do.

1617
01:42:29,880 --> 01:42:31,881
But my family will be home soon.

1618
01:42:32,640 --> 01:42:35,324
Loyal and affectionate, but untrainable.

1619
01:42:36,199 --> 01:42:38,042
Perfectly imperfect.

1620
01:42:38,399 --> 01:42:39,730
They're only human.

1621
01:42:41,439 --> 01:42:42,565
And that's enough for me.

1622
01:42:43,439 --> 01:42:46,125
Merry Christmas to all. Woof!
